{"id":36084,"date":"2021-05-10T13:00:29","date_gmt":"2021-05-10T09:00:29","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=36084"},"modified":"2023-09-19T19:45:58","modified_gmt":"2023-09-19T15:45:58","slug":"no-entry-injustice","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/10\/no-entry-injustice\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Iqtisas: No heavenly entry until wrongs are righted"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Jabir ibn Abdullah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Allah will gather the servants naked, uncircumcised, and destitute.<\/strong>\u201d We said, \u201cWhat is destitute?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>They will have nothing with them. They will be addressed with a voice heard from afar: I am the King! It is not befitting for any of the people of Paradise to enter Paradise while any of the people of Hellfire seek redress for injustice. It is not befitting for any of the people of Hellfire to enter Hellfire while any of the people of Paradise seek redress from injustice.<\/strong>\u201d I said, \u201cHow is it so? We only come to Allah naked and destitute.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>It is by their good and evil deeds.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 970<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Hasan<\/em> (fair) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u0631\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u064a\u064e\u062d\u065